abstract:
China reports its economy pulled back a bit in third quarter 
as measures to rein in inflation and head off speculation put the brakes on growth; gross domestic product rose at annual rate of 9.1 percent.
snippet: Gross domestic product grew at an annual pace of 9.1 percent in the quarter, as measures to rein in inflation and head off speculation put a brake on growth.
lead_paragraph: Gross domestic product grew at an annual pace of 9.1 percent in the quarter, as measures to rein in inflation and head off speculation put a brake on growth.

headline.main: Still Strong, Economy in China Cools Slightly
headline.print_headline: Still Strong, Economy In China Cools Slightly
headline.seo: Chinese Economy Cools Slightly in Third Quarter
